HEADWORD: Hexacid
<hw>Hex`ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hex-</ets> +
<ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having six atoms or
radicals capable of being replaced by acids; hexatomic; hexavalent; --
said of bases; <as>as, mannite is a <ex>hexacid</ex>
base</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hexactinellid</ent>⟦br⟧
